2019-08-24  Andras Varga

	ide: NED editor: fix "Failed to create the part's controls"

	Due to:

	org.eclipse.core.runtime.AssertionFailedException: assertion failed: file
	is not a NED file, or not parsed yet
	at org.eclipse.core.runtime.Assert.isTrue(Assert.java:110)
	at
	org.omnetpp.ned.core.NedTypeResolver.getNedFileElement(NedTypeResolver.java:246)
	org.eclipse.core.runtime.AssertionFailedException: assertion failed: file
	is not a NED file, or not parsed yet
	at org.eclipse.core.runtime.Assert.isTrue(Assert.java:110)
	at
	org.omnetpp.ned.core.NedTypeResolver.getNedFileElement(NedTypeResolver.java:246)
	at
	org.omnetpp.ned.editor.graph.GraphicalNedEditor.getModel(GraphicalNedEditor.java:608)
	at
	org.omnetpp.ned.editor.graph.GraphicalNedEditor.setInput(GraphicalNedEditor.java:629)
	at
	org.eclipse.gef.ui.parts.GraphicalEditor.init(GraphicalEditor.java:346)
	at
	org.omnetpp.ned.editor.graph.GraphicalNedEditor.init(GraphicalNedEditor.java:216)

	Note:

	   public synchronized NedFileElementEx getNedFileElement(IFile file) {
	       Assert.isTrue(nedFiles.containsKey(file), "file is not a NED file,
	or not parsed yet");
	       return nedFiles.get(file);
	   }

	NedEditorLauncher needs to test the availability of the NED file in the
	same way NED editor does: by checking whether the file was actually
	loaded (whether resolver.nedFiles contains it)

